         <div type="bibliography" subtype="edition">
            <ab>A few words were read in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:bergaigne-1888"/>: <biblScope>88</biblScope></bibl>; partially published, with French translation, in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:aymonier-1891"/>: <biblScope>28-29</biblScope></bibl>; whence, summed up in English, in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:majumdar-1927"/>: <biblScope>207</biblScope></bibl> and <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:golzio-2004"/>: <biblScope>179-180</biblScope></bibl> whence again, with translation into French in <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:schweyer-2005a"/>: <biblScope>95-96</biblScope></bibl>. The present edition and translation after <bibl><ptr target="cic-bibl:ECIC-IV"/>: <biblScope><seg type="check">forthcoming</seg></biblScope></bibl> where we have re-edited the text from the inked EFEO estampage and the stone.</ab>
         </div>        
